        "description": "Hive has implemented Kerberos principal mapping for authentication; the same should be implemented for LDAP authentication.\nBoth Kerberos and LDAP are using Active Directory as a backend to store principals (in many cases), so it's naturally to think this should work for LDAP too.\nFact that this mapping works only for Kerberos and not for LDAP principals, breaks authentication in our organization.",
